                            <comment id="13004480" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 11:32:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree it&apos;s a bug, but I think \D is too wide a match, as it matches space/tab etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Might be better to use \p&lt;/p&gt;
{isL}
&lt;p&gt; (is Unicode letter), but there are possibly other solutions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a public ftp server we can use to test this against?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004482" author="jojo1234" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 11:39:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately this problem occurred with a private ftp server. The account we use is password protected and it&apos;s productive. So it cannot used for tests. I&apos;m sorry.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004502" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 12:03:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you try \p&lt;/p&gt;
{isL}
&lt;p&gt; instead of \D and see if that works?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004522" author="jojo1234" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 13:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;\p&lt;/p&gt;
{isL}
&lt;p&gt; does not work - a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Unparseable regex supplied
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But \p&lt;/p&gt;
{L}
&lt;p&gt; does the job.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004524" author="jojo1234" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 13:03:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;\p&lt;/p&gt;
{IsL}
&lt;p&gt; works, too. Has to be a capital I.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004913" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 01:05:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the end, decided to use \S&lt;/p&gt;
{3}
&lt;p&gt;, because that is what most of the other parsers use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
